Reggaeton and Dance Hall... Soca...there are so many dance forms that are similar to Hip Hop. Like music, various dance genres have their roots in Africa. I'm glad you look further than your trainer who told you adult classes wouldn't like hip hop. I teach people of all ages and abilities, including seniors at the Calabasas Senior Center. One class is Zumba Gold and the other is Dance It Out or Dance Express. I do not go easy on them. Maybe I'll do something 8X instead of 4X. Maybe I"ll avoid too many turns. I do offer modifications and make sure that anything I'm recommending they do is safe. That said, there's no reason why I shouldn't be teaching them Hip Hop, Belly Dance, Burlesque, Bollywood. . . I also vary my music and include songs from many eras, including present-day music. Everyone loves it!!! It's Zumba Gold, not Zumba Old or Zumba Moldy. Everyone needs to try new things to keep their bodies and brains challenged - honestly, #whocares is my main motto. Who cares if you don't get the moves just perfectly right? Who cares if you go the opposite direction? Who cares if you're not as flexible as the other person? What happens if you make a mistake - nothing! Really!
